metadata.name: Luminocity #48
metadata.description:
Millions of lights shine forth from the windows of the city. Who lives behind those windows? What do they see when they look out?

The light shining down from distant stars. Do those stars have planets and cities with lights of their own?

--------------------------

This is a 100% code generated project. Outputs are created in either night, sunrise, or sunset mode and at a default resolution of 1500 x 1000.

Click on the output and use these keys to change it:
'n' - change to night
'u' - change to sunrise
'd' - change to sunset
's' - save at current resolution
'2' - change to  3000 x 2000 resolution
'3' - change to  4500 x 3000 resolution
...
'8' - change to 12000 x 8000 resolution

URL Parameters: You can also set the time and resolution in the url.
To change the time mode append on the end of the url &time=sunset  (or night/sunrise)
To change the resolution append &res=2 (or 3-8)

Copyright 2023 Jeff Clark
--------------------------
100% generative

All drawing and geometric code created by Jeff Clark using standard javascript and canvas 2D api

metadata.name: Puzzles of the mind #186
metadata.description:
This is abstract art based on mathematical structure.
The puzzle of your mind seems broken and rearranged.

Mode has 2 variations.
 - Normal
 - Black
Color has 3 variations.
 - 常磐-tokiwa- (Green)
 - 真朱-shinshu- (Red)
 - 紺碧-konpeki- (Blue)
Color Level has 2 variations.
 - High
 - Low
Square Size has 3 variations.
 - Small
 - Middle
 - Large

Tokiwa is a Japanese word meaning always the same. It's green like the color of evergreen leaves.

Shinshu is a Japanese word that refers to a dull red color like vermilion. It means vermilion in its natural state with nothing mixed in.

Konpeki is a Japanese word that describes a deep blue, very close to azure. It's like a clear sky with summer sunshine.

Controls (in live view):
 - Press [f] to switch full screen on and off
 - Press [s] to download a PNG file with windowsize
 - Press [l] to download a PNG file with large size 4800 pixel (wait a minutes)

Create with p5.js
License: CC BY-NC-SA 4.0

metadata.name: Badgirs City #114
metadata.description:
"I used to live in a small city placed at the center of Iran's plateau with the warmest summer days in the country part; spending most of my childhood with my sweet grandma at her old house. She was always keeping her eyes on me not to get heat stroke at noon playing in the yard when the sun was at its peak glowing furiously. Sundays at noon were my favorite, I used to call them “Ice cream” noons sitting beside the nicest person you could imagine and enjoying a delightful ice cream. You won't know how lovely it was to have an ice cream relaxing under the most enjoyable cold breeze of the tallest windcatcher in the city at her house. "



The Badgirs city is the first collaboration between Fleep and IceRain on Fxhash. The concept was established first with the design of a school with a feeling of safe and nostalgia reminding us of the good memories of our childhood as the grandma’s house and the windcatcher for Fleep.
A windcatcher (Badgir) is an Iranian traditional architectural element in the form of a small tower built on the roof of houses in warm locations to create passive cooling. The collection of Badgirs city is a modern recreational development of those traditional windcatchers designed by Fleep and icerain and exquisitely translated into code by Icerain.

Controls:
[1] Set the resolution to Medium Resolution
[2] Set the resolution to High Resolution

metadata.name: Wandering Nets Redux #18
metadata.description:
Wandering Nets Redux is a reissue of Wandering Nets (March 2022). Due to an unfortunate error in the original piece Wandering Nets no longer displays live inside the current fxhash UI. This restored and updated generative token is offered free to all collectors of the original, with some additional tweaks and capabilities.

January 2023

Original description as below:

- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

Wandering Nets is a digital kinetic light sculpture by Matt Ebb.

Networks of light are created and connected via random walks in space and colour. Emergent structures are revealed by the ambient interaction, tension and collision of these networks within themselves and orbiting shadowed spherical bodies.

The piece is the result of several months of custom development in realtime volume rendering. The scene data is generated in javascript and rendered with a bespoke GLSL raytracer - no external libraries are used.

This is a graphically intensive shader. By default it will adaptively adjust sampling quality to target 30fps, though a reasonably fast GPU is recommended for best results.

Mouse drag: Orbit the camera in 3D to explore compositions
[ and ] keys: Override the adaptive samples per pixel lower or higher to trade noise for framerate

March 2022

Update -
spacebar: Disturb the light positions

metadata.name: Holy Moly #38
metadata.description:
The idea for this project came from a common drawing exercise where different shapes and shading are used to create the illusion of depth. Here I'm using four layers containing various types of holes. Some are recognizable primitive shapes but others are organic in form or distorted. There are ten features reported that affect the character of each output.

To change the resolution:
1. Click on the image
2. Use the keys 2-8 to change resolution, '2' will produce a 2000 x 2000 image (default), '3' a 3000 x 3000 image etc
3. Once generated press 'S' to save as a png

Jeff Clark
December 2022
--------------------------
All drawing and geometric code created by Jeff Clark using vanilla javascript except for:

- perlin.js from https://codepen.io/sixsided/pen/emxxea.js

metadata.name: Love Poem #38
metadata.description:
Love is a very complex feeling,

The definition of love would be different if we ask 300 people in the same room. Although uniquely different to each other, most people would agree on how complex love could be, especially if it’s directed towards something that’s not quite humane; neither alive, nor is it dead.

“Love Poem” is one of the conveyor and translator of that feeling.

The unique and abstracted iterations of different love poems made through the distinctive pixelart style of MEK.txt and the coding diligence and brilliance of IceRain, are the innocent attempt the two brewed to help people convey and interpret how their form of love poems could be.

• • •

All of the visuals in this project are 100% code.

[s/S] to save the image

metadata.name: - Still-Life with Flowers - #3
metadata.description:
- Still-Life with Flowers - a generative take on a classic artistic motif.  

The term ‘still-life’ derives from the Dutch word ‘stilleven’, roughly translated it means ‘arrangement of inanimate objects’. Over the centuries, artists have used the ‘still-life genre to try out new techniques and experiment with composition and arrangements. 

- Still-Life with Flowers - is my attempt to (humbly) follow in the footsteps of the artists that contributed to the still life genre and made it into the iconic artistic style it is today.


- Still-Life with Flowers - consists of 256 Flower arrangements (mintable iterations) celebrating compositional experiments and the artistic arrangement of inanimate objects !

For every iteration, over 200 random number generators (fxrand) are triggered to create a unique floral arrangement. (no images were used to create this Artwork)

—

Press R to toggle the animation on / off

Press X to reset 

—

I want to thank everyone who helped me realize this project.
(you know who you are ; )
This project took a long time to make, it was a pretty bumpy road and I could not have done it without your generosity and patience ! 

Made with cables.gl (check it out, it is amazing !)

metadata.name: Sketch Block #151
metadata.description:
At the heart of "Sketch Block" is the concept of the sketch block itself - a blank canvas where the possibilities for creation are endless. The name "Sketch Block" reflects the process of creation that inspired the token's design. Like an artist's sketchbook, the token captures the playful experimentation and exploration that underlies the creative process.

The hand-drawn style gives a playful feel to the project, with each shape looking as if it was quickly drawn onto the canvas. Along with the use of vibrant color palettes with tones ranging from soft pastels to bold and bright tones, the projects can produce a wide range of different results.


----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

User Controls:

- Press 'h' to save the image
